{"title":"Curve AIR Kev Ti + Carbon Gravel Bike, Huge Walmer Carbon Bar Tease & Gearbox GMX+","link":"https://bikerumor.com/curve-air-kev-ti-carbon-gravel-bike-walmer-carbon-bar-gearbox-gmx/","date":1692197931000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-titaniumcarbon-version-of-GXR-gravel-bike-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Curve Cycling has got a lot going on, with an all-new AIR Kev gravel bike mixing it up in titanium &amp; carbon, a new prototype of their mega-wide Walmer flared dropbar in carbon, and a next-gen version of their titanium GMX+ adventure bike with an all-new Effigear Mimic 9-speed gearbox. That’s just a few of the things they were showing at the 2023 Handmade Bicycle Show Australia, but now that  you can actually pre-order the limited first run of Air Kev, it’s time we took a closer look… </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Curve AIR Kev titanium &amp; carbon version of GXR gravel bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, angled\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike_angled-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption><em>all c. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/curvecycling/\" target=\"_blank\">Curve Cycling</a></em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Curve’s most popular bike is their titanium GXR gravel cross racer, <em>aka</em> Kevin. It’s their simple no-nonsense do-it-all gravel racing and bikepacking bike, built in titanium to last a lifetime. Well, in celebration of their 10-year anniversary, they decided to add a little bit of extra flair, to lighten up the bike and give it a racier race bike edition, based on the carbon seat tube concept from their limited edition Belgie AIR endurance road race bike, with carbon bonding in-house in Melbourne, Australia. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter the AIR Kev.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, seatpost\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_seatpost-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Curve AIR Kev gets the same basic geometry and generous tire clearance (max 700×45 or 650×2.2″). But it replaces the frame’s titanium seattube with a bonded-in carbon tube. Then, it gets a Curve custom 27.2mm carbon seatpost with a 3D-printed titanium head &amp; ENVE guts. It gets more neatly integrated conventional internal cable routing (but not through the headset), also through the BB &amp; chainstay via a new 1-sided chainstay yoke. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, T-Type derailleur\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_T-type-transmission-derailleur-1152x1536.jpg 1152w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, 3d-printed dropout\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_dropout-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame also features new machined titanium dropouts with UDH or T-Type derailleur compatibility, and a direct flat mount 160 rear brake mount.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, crankset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_crankset-1152x1536.jpg 1152w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, fork detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_fork-detail-1152x1536.jpg 1152w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, it pares the plethora of mounts back to the bare essentials for a gravel race bike – two cages in the frame, one mount under the downtube and another on top of the toptube. The AIR Kev also gets a custom Ride 415 full carbon fork with internal cable routing and a drop out flip chip, but no bikepacking mounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, complete\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_complete-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This show bike also features a new evolution of Curve G4.5T carbon wheels with a new straight-out-of-the-mold finish, and laser-etched graphics. Curve says getting ready of post-mold finishing meant an 8% weight reduction vs. their current G4T wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, bikepacking loaded\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_loaded-bikepacking-bike-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Curve AIR Kev isn’t officially available yet, but Curve is taking pre-order slots <a href=\"mailto:sales@curvecycling.com⁠\" target=\"_blank\"><em>via email</em>.</a> Apparently, just 23 are being produced in the first batch this year, so get in touch if you need to have one.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1250\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Cycling AIR Kev prototype titanium and carbon version of the GXR gravel cross race bike, Rhino bikepacking Europe\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe-297x265.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe-800x714.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe-120x107.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-AIR-Kev-prototype-titanium-and-carbon-GXR-gravel-bike-evolution_Rhino-bikepacking-Europe-768x686.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This prototype by the way is being pedaled around Europe as we speak, as Curve’s sales director <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/flinnryan/\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Flinn</a> is back on the road – bikepacking around to meet dealers and Curve owners for rides all summer!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Prototype Walmer Carbon flared adventure gravel handlebar</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1350\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar.jpg\" alt=\"Curve prototype Walmer Carbon flared adventure gravel handlebar detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar.jpg 1350w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar-297x264.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar-800x711.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar-120x107.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar-768x683.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, this bike is sporting a prototype 46cm Walmer carbon ultra-flared dropbar – with a 31.8mm clamp that quickly tapers down to a more ergonomic shape on the tops with integrated routing channels. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail.jpg\" alt=\"Curve prototype Walmer Carbon flared adventure gravel handlebar, detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail-297x134.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail-800x360.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail-120x54.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail-768x346.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_detail-1536x691.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on the popular but niche <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-curve-walmer-bar-is-a-wide-or-super-wide-flared-dropbar-for-off-road-adventures/\" target=\"_blank\">6066 alloy Walmer bars</a> that we’ve previously tested, this carbon prototype likely shares the same generous 29° flare to compact drops, plus a small 7° backsweep up top. That means this 46cm bar (measured center-center at the hoods) is likely a full 61cm outside-outside at the end of its drops. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide.jpg\" alt=\"Curve prototype Walmer Carbon flared adventure gravel handlebar, 46cm wide\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Cycling-prototype-Walmer-Carbon-flared-adventure-gravel-handlebar_46cm-wide-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>See it really is huge. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>GMX+ Gearbox v2 adventure bikepacking concept bike</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox.jpg\" alt=\"Curve GMX+ Gearbox v2 adventure bikepacking concept bike, Effigear Mimic 9-speed gearbox\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Last summer Curve built a gearbox concept iteration of their Gravel MonsterCross <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/curve-gmx-goes-big-on-limited-edition-limitless-titanium-off-road-bikepacking-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">GMX+ bike</a> with a Pinion to hash out the value in alt drivetrain. This year, they have a new Gearbox GMX+ bike, but with a new <a href=\"https://www.effigear.com/en/135-The-Mimic.html\" target=\"_blank\">Effigear Mimic</a> 9-speed gearbox that they say works even easier with just a single cable pulled by a SRAM 11sp DoubleTap shifter making for a cleaner, simpler setup. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Curve GMX+ Gearbox v2 adventure bikepacking concept bike, Effigear Mimic 9-speed gearbox\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_Effigear-Mimic-9-speed-gearbox-detail-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a French-made gearbox that debuted in 2012, which we weren’t already familiar with. But, it’s less than 2kg; it uses the same mounting as Pinion; is directly compatible with SRAM X trigger shifters, SRAM Rival 11sp shifters, or Campy Centaur levers; and offers a 469% gear ratio in 9-speeds. Sounds interesting, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar.jpg\" alt=\"Curve GMX+ Gearbox v2 adventure bikepacking concept bike, 50cm Walmer Carbon prototype\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Gearbox-GMX-Plus-v2-adventure-bikepacking-concept-bike_50cm-Walmer-Carbon-bar-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Gearbox GMX+ Mimic is still just a prototype that you can’t yet buy from Curve. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But under that bar bag made by <a href=\"https://www.buckitbelts.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BUCK!T</a> from recycled Vittoria gravel tires, it’s also sporting a wider 50cm version of that same prototype Walmer Carbon flared gravel dropbar (<em>65cm ? outside</em>). That suggests to us that Curve is likely to make these carbon Walmer bars available pretty soon.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Belgie AIR MN road bike</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia.jpg\" alt=\"Curve Belgie AIR MN road bike, made-in-Australia\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Curve-Belgie-AIR-MN-pre-production-titanium-and-carbon-road-bike-made-in-Australia-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, the Curve Belgie AIR MN road bike. The all-road Belgie was the first to get a race-focused AIR version with a carbon seattube to make it more of a dedicated road bike. This pre-production version takes the Belgie AIR to the next level, in an attempt to see how Curve can bring frame production back to their Melbourne, Australia base. To do that, the Belgie AIR MN takes advantage of newly refined 3D-printed ti parts like: a 1-piece headtube to integrate fully internal cable routing through the headset, sleek UDH compatible dropouts, a 3d-printed ti front derailleur hanger developed especially for SRAM AXS shift stiffness, and a custom made carbon integrated seat post and printed ti topper.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.curvecycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\">CurveCycling.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/curve-air-kev-ti-carbon-gravel-bike-walmer-carbon-bar-gearbox-gmx/\">Curve AIR Kev Ti + Carbon Gravel Bike, Huge Walmer Carbon Bar Tease &amp; Gearbox GMX+</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"932ea605d944a9ab7e158086950fe2e61e8aa101296705dc1934d6634ea88892","category":"Cycling"}